The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Feb. 27 (PTI): The government today announced that it will double compensation to the kin of hit-and-run accident victims on national highways. Minister of state for road transport and highways K.H. Muniyappa informed the Lok Sabha that the ex-gratia payment to the victims kin in such cases would be Rs 50,000 against the current amount of Rs 25,000.          
	The minister also said that general damages in case of pain and suffering would be up to Rs 5,000. There is no such provision at present.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The CBI will soon question former defence minister George Fernandes and former naval chief Admiral Susheel Kumar for their alleged role in the Rs 1150-crore deal to purchase the Barak Missile System from Israel during NDA rule in 2000. The CBI has completed questioning arms dealer Suresh Nanda whose passport has been suspended for four weeks.                   
	Chennai (PTI): Union minister Dasari Narayanaraos son Harihara Prabhu denied on Wednesday that he was kidnapped from a hotel room in Chitoor on Tuesday. Prabhu told a news channel that he had come to Chennai on his own, disputing his estranged wife Susheelas complaint to police that he had been kidnapped.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Raj Thackeray has received an anonymous letter that warned he would be killed if he continued with his tirade against north Indians, the Maharashtra Navnirman Sena leaders associates said on Wednesday. The letter said Thackerays campaign against migrants from Uttar Pradesh and Bihar was wrong, and claimed that a contract to kill him had been given to a sharpshooter.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): Ind ia is planning to launch a satellite to study the sun, the Lok Sabha said on Wednesday. Satellite Aditya will study the corona, the outermost region of the sun, and other parameters of space weather, minister of state in the PMO Prithviraj Chavan said.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): Gangster Dawood Ibrahims nephew Sajid Wagle was arrested on Tuesday for allegedly trying to extort money from a cable operator.                                                                                                                           
